benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Retrieve account tags

covered: Valid Request: The happy path (TC01) demonstrates successful retrieval with required path parameter.
Empty Response: TC06 covers an account with no tags returning an empty array.
Query Parameters: Tests cover various valid/invalid query parameters (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC14, TC15, TC23).
Authorization: Tests for missing/invalid tokens (TC12, TC13) cover unauthorized scenarios.
Error Handling: Tests for non-existent account (TC07 404), invalid accountId formats (TC08, TC20, TC21, TC22), downstream failures (TC24).
Other non-functional/scenario: API unavailable (TC11), high-load/performance with large data (TC16), concurrency (TC17), and regression scenarios (TC18, TC19, TC24, TC25).
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for pagination behavior with large datasets.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting/throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests asserting caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Authorization: No explicit 403 forbidden scenario; tests mostly cover 401 Unauthorized.
Edge-case: Some boundary tests are ambiguous (TC23 maximum length) as to exact status.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests (page size, page token) to ensure proper handling of large result sets.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify throttling behavior under burst traffic.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag and Cache-Control) and cache-invalidations.
Add a dedicated 403 forbidden test to cover insufficient permissions.
Add end-to-end test with transient downstream failure and retry behavior.
